<li>Butler, J., 2006, &lsquo;Critique, Coercion, and Sacred Life in
Benjamin&rsquo;s &ldquo;Critique of Violence&rdquo;&rsquo;, in
<em>Political Theologies: Public Religions in a Post-Secular
World</em>, ed. Hent de Vries and Lawrence Sullivan, New York: Fordham
University Press, pp. 201&ndash;219.</li>

<li>Caygill, H., 1994, &lsquo;Benjamin, Heidegger and the Destruction
of Tradition&rsquo;, in Benjamin and Osborne 1994/2000, pp.
1&ndash;31.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, <em>Walter Benjamin: The Colour of
Experience</em>, London: Routledge.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2004, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s
Concept of Cultural History,&rsquo; in Ferris 2004, pp.
73&ndash;96.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, &lsquo;Non-Messianic Political
Theology in Benjamin&rsquo;s &ldquo;On the Concept of
History&rdquo;&rsquo;, in Benjamin, A. 2005b, pp. 215&ndash;226.</li>

<li>Charles, M., 2013, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin and the Inhumanities:
Towards a Pedagogical Anti-Nietzscheanism&rsquo;, in <em>Pedagogies of
Disaster</em>, ed. Jenkins, N., van Gerven Oei, V. W. J., and Staley
Groves, A., Brookyln, NY: Punctum, pp. 331&ndash;354.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2018, &lsquo;Secret Signals from Another
World: Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s Theory of Innervation&rsquo;, <em>New
German Critique</em>, 45(3): 39&ndash;72.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, <em>Modernism Between Benjamin and
Goethe</em>, London: Bloomsbury.</li>

<li>Chisholm, D., 2009, &lsquo;Benjamin&rsquo;s Gender, Sex, and
Eros&rsquo;, in Goebel 2009, pp. 246&ndash;272.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, <em>Queer constellations: subcultural
space in the wake of the city</em>, Minneapolis: University of
Minnesota Press.</li>

<li>Chow, R., 1989, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s Love Affair with
Death&rsquo;, <em>New German Critique</em>, 48: 63&ndash;86.</li>

<li>Clark, T. J, 2003, &lsquo;Should Benjamin Have Read Marx&rsquo;,
<em>Boundary 2</em>, 30(1): 31&ndash;49; reprinted in Osborne 2005,
III: 81&ndash;96.</li>

<li>Cohen, M., 1993, <em>Profane Illumination: Walter Benjamin and the
Paris of Surrealist Revolution</em>, Berkeley &amp; Los Angeles:
University of California Press.</li>

<li>Cowan, B., 1981, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s Theory of
Allegory&rsquo;, <em>New German Critique</em>, 22: 109&ndash;122.</li>

<li>Derrida, J., 1990, &lsquo;Force of Law: The &ldquo;Mystical
Foundations of Authority&rdquo;&rsquo;, trans. Mary Quaintance,
<em>Cardozo Law Review</em>, 11: 973&ndash;1045, reprinted in Osborne
2005, 1: 398&ndash;432.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1994, <em>Spectres of Marx: the state of
the debt, the work of mourning, and the New International</em>, trans.
P. Kamuf, London: Routledge.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, <em>The Politics of Friendship</em>,
trans. G. Collins, London &amp; New York: Verso.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &lsquo;Marx and Sons&rsquo;, in
<em>Ghostly demarcations: a symposium on Jacques Derrida&rsquo;s
Spectres of Marx</em>, ed. M. Sprinker, London &amp; New York: Verso,
pp. 213&ndash;269.</li>

<li>Didi-Huberman, G., 2005, &lsquo;The Supposition of the Aura: The
Now, the Then and Modernity&rsquo;, in Benjamin, A., 2005b, pp.
2&ndash;18.</li>

<li>Eagleton, T., 1981, <em>Walter Benjamin, Or, Towards a
Revolutionary Criticism</em>, London: NLB.</li>

<li>Eiland, H., 2011, &lsquo;Translator&rsquo;s Introduction&rsquo;,
in EW, pp. 1&ndash;13.</li>

<li>Erazo-Heufelder, J., 2017, <em>Der argentinische Kr&ouml;sus:
Kleine Wirtschaftsgeschichte der Frankfurter Schule</em>, Berlin:
Berenberg Verlag.</li>

<li>Ferber, I., 2013, <em>Philosophy and Melancholy: Benjamin&rsquo;s
Early Reflections on Theater and Language</em>, Stanford: Stanford
University Press.</li>

<li>Feuer, M., 2018, &lsquo;Discovering the Truth of Sancho Panza: The
Meaning of Comedy in Adorno&rsquo;s and Benjamin&rsquo;s Divergent
Readings of Don Quixote&rsquo;, in <em>Benjamin, Adorno, and the
Experience of Literature</em>, ed. McCall, C. and Ross, N., New York:
Routledge, pp. 126&ndash;140.</li>

<li>Fleck, C., 2023, &lsquo;The Political Economy of the Frankfurt
School&rsquo;, <em>Society</em>, 60: 106&ndash;113.</li>

<li>Friedlander, E., 2012, <em>Walter Benjamin: A Philosophical
Portrait</em>, Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Frisby, D., 1996, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s Prehistory of
Modernity as Anticipation of Postmodernity? Some Methodological
Reflections&rsquo;, in Fischer 1996, pp. 15&ndash;32.</li>

<li>Fuld, W., 1981, &lsquo;Walter Benjamins Beziehung zu Ludwig
Klages&rsquo;, <em>Akzente</em>, 28(3): 274&ndash;287.</li>

<li>Gilloch, G., 2000, <em>Walter Benjamin: Critical
Constellations</em>, Cambridge: Polity.</li>

<li>Goebel, R. J., 2001, <em>Benjamin heute. Gro&szlig;stadtdiskurs,
Postkolonialit&auml;t und Flanerie zwischen den Kulturen</em>, Munich:
Iudicium.</li>

<li>Greenberg, U. E., 2008, &lsquo;Orthodox violence:
&lsquo;&lsquo;Critique of Violence&rsquo;&rsquo; and Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s Jewish political theology,&rsquo; <em>History of
European Ideas</em>, 34: 324&ndash;333.</li>

<li>Habermas, J., 1983, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin: Consciousness-raising
or rescuing critique&rsquo;, in <em>Philosophical-Political
Profiles</em>, trans. Frederick G. Lawrence, Cambridge, MA. &amp;
London: MIT Press, pp. 129&ndash;163, reprinted in Osborne 2005, I:
107&ndash;136.</li>

<li>Hamacher, W., 1991, &lsquo;Afformative, Strike&rsquo;, trans. Dana
Hollander, <em>Cardozo Law Review Review</em>, 13: 1132&ndash;1157,
reprinted in Benjamin, A. and Osborne 1994/2000: 110&ndash;138.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, &lsquo;Guilt History:
Benjamin&rsquo;s Sketch &ldquo;Capitalism as Religion&rdquo;&rsquo;,
<em>Diacritics</em>, 32(3/4): 81&ndash;106.</li>

<li>Hansen, M., 1987, &lsquo;Benjamin, Cinema and Experience:
&ldquo;The Blue Flower in the Land of Technology&rdquo;&rsquo;,
<em>New German Critique</em>, 40: 179&ndash;224; reprinted in Osborne
2005, II: 253&ndash;290.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, <em>Cinema and Experience: Siegfried
Kracauer, Walter Benjamin, and Theodor W. Adorno</em>, Los Angeles
&amp; London: University of California Press.</li>

<li>Hanssen, B., 1995, &lsquo;Philosophy at Its Origin: Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s Prologue to the <em>Ursprung des deutschen
Trauerspiels</em>&rsquo;, <em>MLN</em>, 110(4): 809&ndash;833.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, <em>Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s Other
History: Of Stones, Animals, Human Beings, and Angels</em>, Berkeley,
Los Angeles &amp; London: University of California Press.#</li>

<li>Hill, S. R. and Gillespie, S. H., 2019, &lsquo;On Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s Legacy: A Correspondence Between Hannah Arendt and
Theodor Adorno&rsquo;, <em>LA Review of Books</em>.</li>

<li>Hodge, J., 2005, &lsquo;The Timing of Elective Affinity: Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s Strong Aesthetics&rsquo;, in Benjamin, A., 2005a, pp.
14&ndash;31.</li>

<li>Holz, H. H., 1992, <em>Philosophie der zersplittern Welt:
Reflexionen &uuml;ber Walter Benjamin</em>, Bonn:
Pahl-Rugenstein.</li>

<li>Kang, J., 2014, <em>Walter Benjamin and the Media: the Spectacle
of Modernity</em>, Cambridge: Polity.</li>

<li>Khatib, S., 2013, &lsquo;The Messianic Without Messianism: Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s Materialist Theology&rsquo;, <em>Anthropology &amp;
Materialism</em>, 1. doi:10.4000/am.159</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013, <em>Teleologie ohne Endzweck. Walter
Benjamins Ent-stellung des Messianischen</em>, Marburg: Tectum.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, &lsquo;Society and Violence&rsquo;,
in <em>The SAGE Handbook of Frankfurt School Critical Theory</em>, ed.
Best, B., Bonefeld, W. and O&rsquo;Kane, C., Los Angeles, London, New
Delhi, Singapore: Sage, pp. 607&ndash;624.</li>

<li>Kittsteiner, H. D., 1986, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s
Historicism&rsquo;, <em>New German Critique</em>, 39:
179&ndash;215.</li>

<li>Kohlenbach, M., 2002, <em>Walter Benjamin: Self-Reference and
Religiosity</em>, Basingstoke, England and New York, NJ: Palgrave
Macmillan.</li>

<li>Kolour, J. M.,2023, &lsquo;The politics of Benjamin&rsquo;s
laughter at melancholy&rsquo;, <em>Critique</em>, 51(4):
459&ndash;485.</li>

<li>Lacoue-Labarthe, P., 1992, &lsquo;Introduction to Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s The Concept of Art Criticism in German
Romanticism&rsquo;, <em>Studies in Romanticism</em>, 31(4):
421&ndash;432, reprinted in Hanssen and Benjamin, A. 2002, pp.
9&ndash;18.</li>

<li>Lambrianou, N., 2005, &lsquo;Neo-Kantianism and Messianism: Origin
and Interruption in Hermann Cohen and Walter Benjamin&rsquo;, in
Osborne 2005, I: 82&ndash;104.</li>

<li>Lebovic, N., 2013, <em>The Philosophy of Life and Death: Ludwig
Klages and the Rise of Nazi Biopolitics</em>, New York &amp;
Basingstoke: Palgrave Macmillan.</li>

<li>Leslie, E., 2000, <em>Walter Benjamin: Overpowering
Conformism</em>, London: Pluto.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, &lsquo;Revolutionary Potential and
Walter Benjamin: A Postwar Reception History&rsquo;, in <em>Critical
Companion to Contemporary Marxism</em>, eds. Jacques Bidet and Stavis
Kouvelakis, Leiden: Brill, pp. 549&ndash;566.</li>

<li>Lewis, T. E., 2020, <em>Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s Antifascist
Education: From Riddles to Radio</em>, Albany: SUNY.</li>

<li>Lindner, B. (ed.), 2006, <em>Benjamin-Handbuch. Leben, Werk,
Wirkung</em>, Stuttgart: Metzler.</li>

<li>Liska, V., 2009, &lsquo;The Legacy of Benjamin&rsquo;s Messianism:
Giorgio Agamben and Other Contenders&rsquo;, in Goebel 2009, pp.
195&ndash;215.</li>

<li>L&oacute;pez, N., 2022, &lsquo;De La &ldquo;Humaneidad
No-Incrementada&rdquo; al &ldquo;Humanism Real De Lo No-Humano&rdquo;:
La Pol&eacute;mica de Walter Benjamin con el &Uuml;bermensch&rsquo;,
<em>Eidos</em>, 38: 98&ndash;122.</li>

<li>L&ouml;wy, M., 2005, <em>Fire Alarm: Reading Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s</em> &lsquo;On the Concept of History&rsquo;, trans.
Chris Turner, London &amp; New York: Verso.</li>

<li>McCole, J. J., 1993, <em>Walter Benjamin and the Antinomies of
Tradition</em>, Ithaca, NY: Cornell University Press.</li>

<li>McFarland, J., 2013, <em>Constellation: Friedrich Nietzsche and
Walter Benjamin in the Now-Time of History</em>, New York: Fordham
University Press.</li>

<li>Menninghaus, W., 2002, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin&rsquo;s Exposition
of the Romantic Theory of Reflection&rsquo;, trans. Robert J. Kiss, in
Hanssen and Benjamin, A. 2002, pp. 19&ndash;50, reprinted in Osborne
2005, I: 25&ndash;62.</li>

<li>Mulder, B., 2015, <em>De nazi&rsquo;s te slim af zijn. Sophie
Louisa Kwaak en het kapitaal van de Frankfurter Schule</em>,
Gorredijk, the Netherlands: Bornmeer.</li>

<li>Newman, J. O., 2011, <em>Benjamin&rsquo;s Library: Modernity,
Nation, and the Baroque</em>, Ithaca, NY: Cornell University
Press.</li>

<li>Osborne, P., 1995, <em>The Politics of Time: Modernity and
Avant-Garde</em>, London &amp; New York: Verso.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &lsquo;Philosophy after Theory:
Transdisciplinarity and the New&rsquo;, in <em>Theory After
&lsquo;Theory&rsquo;</em>, eds. Jane Elliott and Derek Attridge,
Abingdon: Routledge, pp. 19&ndash;33.</li>

<li>Procyshyn, A., 2014, &lsquo;Manifest Reason: Walter Benjamin on
Violence and Collective Agency&rsquo;, <em>Constellations</em>, 21(3):
390&ndash;400.</li>

<li>Raz-Krakotzkin, A., 2013, &lsquo;On the Right Side of the
Barricades: Walter Benjamin, Gershom Scholem and Zionism&rsquo;,
<em>Comparative Literature</em>, 65(3): 363&ndash;381.</li>

<li>Rrenban, M., 2005, <em>Wild, Unforgettable Philosophy: In Early
Works of Walter Benjamin</em>, Lanham &amp; Oxford: Lexington
Books.</li>

<li>Roff, S. L., 2004, &lsquo;Benjamin and Psychoanalysis&rsquo;, in
Ferris 2004, pp. 115&ndash;133.</li>

<li>Schmitt, C., 1956, <em>Hamlet or Hecuba: the intrusion of time
into the play</em>, trans. D. Pan &amp; J. Rust, New York: Telos
Press, 2009.</li>

<li>Sch&ouml;ttker, D. and Wizisla, E. (eds.), 2017, <em>Arendt und
Benjamin: Texte, Briefe, Dokumente</em>, Frankfurt am Main:
Suhrkamp.</li>

<li>Steiner, U., 2001, &lsquo;The True Politician: Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s Concept of the Political&rsquo;, trans. C. Sample,
<em>New German Critique</em>, 83: 43&ndash;88.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, <em>Walter Benjamin: An Introduction
to his Work and Thought</em>, trans. Michael Winkler, Chicago &amp;
London: University of Chicago Press.</li>

<li>Tiedemann, R., 1983&ndash;4, &lsquo;Historical Materialism or
Political Messianism? An Interpretation of the Theses &ldquo;On the
Concept of History&rdquo;&rsquo;, in Smith 1989, pp. 175&ndash;209,
reprinted in Osborne 2005, I: 137&ndash;168.</li>

<li>Tomba, M., 2009, &lsquo;Another Kind of <em>Gewalt</em>: Beyond
Law. Re-Reading Walter Benjamin&rsquo;, <em>Historical
Materialism</em>, 17(1): 126&ndash;144.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, <em>La vera politica. Kant e
Benjamin: la possibilit&agrave; della giustizia</em>, Macerata:
Quodlibet.</li>

<li>Weber, S., 2008, <em>Benjamin&rsquo;s abilities</em>, Cambridge,
MA., &amp; London: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Weigel, S., 1996, <em>Body- and Image-Space: Re-Reading Walter
Benjamin</em>, London &amp; New York: Routledge.</li>

<li>Wohlfarth, I., 1978, &lsquo;On the Messianic Structure of
Benjamin&rsquo;s Last Reflections&rsquo;, <em>Glyph</em>, 3:
148&ndash;212; reprinted in Osborne 2005, I: 169&ndash;231.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1992, &lsquo;The Politics of Youth: Walter
Benjamin&rsquo;s Reading of The Idiot&rsquo;, <em>Diacritics</em>, 22
(3/4): 160&ndash;172.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin and the Idea
of Technological Eros: A Tentative Reading of <em>Zum
Planetarium</em>&rsquo;, <em>Benjamin Studies/Studien</em>, 1:
65&ndash;109.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008&ndash;9, &lsquo;Walter Benjamin and
the Red Army Faction&rsquo;, Parts, 1&ndash;3, <em>Radical
Philosophy</em>, 152 (Part 1, Nov/Dec 2008): 7&ndash;19; 153 (Part 2,
Jan/Feb 2009): 13&ndash;26; 154 (Part 3, March/April 2009)
9&ndash;24.</li>

<li>Wolin, R., 1994, <em>An Aesthetics of Redemption</em>, Berkeley
&amp; Los Angeles: University of California Press.</li>
</ul>
